ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a clearer picture. Let me analyze the issues:\n\n1. **BDD 
tests failing**: The `tests/bdd/step-definitions/bdd-setup.js` requires `Matchin
gController` and `MatchingService` from `apps/api/dist/modules/matching/`, but t
he matching module doesn\'t exist yet in this branch. This causes 26 BDD tests t
o fail because the BDD setup file is shared across all step definitions and fail
s at module resolution.\n\n2. **ProfileCompletionGuard not applied**: The guard 
is created but not actually mounted on any matching controllers. However, the ma
tching module doesn\'t exist in this branch either, so this might be acceptable 
for now, but it should be noted.\n\n3. **Full chain completeness**: The PR inclu
des DB (migration, entities), API (profile, oss, photo controllers, service, gua
rd), Mobile (setup page, edit page, bloc, repository), Design System (new molecu
les, widgetbook), shared types (PhotoResponse added), docs (profile.md, api cont
racts). This looks comprehensive.\n\n4. **Contract consistency**: The OpenAPI co
ntract `profile.yaml` includes `PhotoResponse`, and the generated shared types i
nclude it. The DTOs on the backend also match. Need to check if `UpdateProfileRe
quest` in the contract matches the backend DTO. Looking at the API contract, `Up
dateProfileRequest` has `required: [nickname, gender, birth_date, latitude, long
itude]`, but the backend `UpdateProfileDto` has all fields optional (with `@IsOp
tional()`). This is a mismatch! The contract says POST uses `UpdateProfileReques
t` but the backend `CreateProfileDto` has required fields without `@IsOptional()
`. Actually, the contract uses `UpdateProfileRequest` for both POST and PATCH, b
ut the backend has separate `CreateProfileDto` (all required) and `UpdateProfile
Dto` (all optional). The contract should probably have a `CreateProfileRequest` 
separate from `UpdateProfileRequest`, or `UpdateProfileRequest` should not have 
required fields if it\'s used for PATCH.\n\nWait, looking more carefully:\n- API
contract `profile.yaml`: `UpdateProfileRequest` has required fields `nickname, g
ender, birth_date, latitude, longitude`\n- Backend `create-profile.dto.ts`: `Cre
ateProfileDto` has all those fields required (no `@IsOptional()`)\n- Backend `up
date-profile.dto.ts`: `UpdateProfileDto` has `@IsOptional()` on everything\n\nBu
t the contract uses `UpdateProfileRequest` for both POST and PATCH. This is tech
nically incorrect because PATCH should allow partial updates. However, since POS
T in the backend requires all fields, the contract is "strict enough" for POST b
ut too strict for PATCH. This is a contract-DTO mismatch.\n\n5. **Missing `prefe
rred_age_min/max` vs `age_range_min/max`**: The exec plan mentions `preferred_ag
e_min?` and `preferred_age_max?` but the code uses `age_range_min` and `age_rang
e_max`. This is consistent across DTOs and contracts, so it\'s fine - just diffe
rent from the exec plan draft.\n\n6. **Age calculator**: The exec plan wanted `a
pps/api/src/common/utils/age.util.ts` and `age.util.spec.ts`, but the code has `
age-calculator.ts` and `age-calculator.spec.ts`. This is a minor naming discrepa
ncy but the functionality is there and tested.\n\n7. **BDD step definitions file
naming**: The exec plan mentions `profile.steps.ts` but the actual files are `pr
ofile-step-defs.js` and `profile_*.steps.js`. This is acceptable since the actua
l implementation uses the project\'s convention.\n\n8. **ProfileSetupPage using 
`UpdateProfileRequest` for creation**: The mobile `ProfileSetupPage` sends `Upda
teProfileRequest` to `SaveProfile` event, which calls `createProfile` in the rep
ository. This is a bit odd but works because the generated models only have `Upd
ateProfileRequest`. Looking at the generated Dart code, there\'s no `CreateProfi
leRequest` - the API contract only defines `UpdateProfileRequest`. This is becau
se the OpenAPI contract only has `UpdateProfileRequest`. So the mobile is constr
ained by the contract.\n\n9. **Widgetbook registration**: New molecules are regi
stered in widgetbook. ✅\n\n10. **Design assets**: `.design-assets.txt` is empty
, no design assets to check against.\n\n11. **DB Migration**: There\'s a migrati
on `20250413000000-AddAvatarUrlAndPhotoUrlsToUserProfiles.ts` but it only adds `
avatar_url`. The `photo_urls` field is NOT in `user_profiles` - instead there\'s
a separate `user_photos` table. The migration name is misleading. Actually looki
ng at the entity, `user_profiles` doesn\'t have `photo_urls` JSON column. The mi
gration name says "AddAvatarUrlAndPhotoUrls" but only adds `avatar_url`. This is
misleading but the actual architecture (separate `user_photos` table) is better.
\n\n12. **Profile module imports AuthModule**: `ProfileModule` imports `AuthModu
le` just to get `TypeOrmModule.forFeature([UserProfileEntity])` exported from it
. This is a bit of a circular dependency smell but technically works since `Auth
Module` exports `TypeOrmModule`. However, `ProfileModule` should probably import
`TypeOrmModule.forFeature([UserProfileEntity])` directly instead of relying on A
uthModule.\n\nWait, looking at `profile.module.ts`:\n```typescript\nimports: [Au
thModule, TypeOrmModule.forFeature([UserPhotoEntity])],\n```\nBut `ProfileServic
e` uses `UserProfileEntity` repository. It gets it from `AuthModule` which expor
ts `TypeOrmModule.forFeature([UserEntity, UserProfileEntity])`. This is an archi
tectural smell - Profile module should own its own entity imports.\n\n13. **Miss
ing `@UsePipes(ValidationPipe)` on controllers?** Looking at the profile control
ler, there\'s no `@UsePipes(new ValidationPipe({ transform: true }))` or similar
. Other controllers in the project might have it. Let me check the auth controll
er.\n\nActually, looking at `profile.controller.ts`, there\'s no `ValidationPipe
`. The DTOs have `class-validator` decorators but without the validation pipe th
ey won\'t be enforced. Let me check if there\'s a global pipe.\n\nLooking at `ap
ps/api/src/main.ts` or similar... Let me check.\n\n14. **OSS DTO ContentType enu
m**: The `UploadUrlDto` uses an enum `ContentType` with values `jpeg = "image/jp
eg"`, `png = "image/png"`. The `@IsEnum(ContentType)` validator will check that 
the value matches the enum values, but when the client sends `"image/jpeg"`, it 
should work. However, `class-validator` with enums can be tricky. Let me see if 
this works correctly.\n\nActually, `class-validator`\'s `@IsEnum()` checks again
st the enum values. Since `ContentType.jpeg = "image/jpeg"`, passing `"image/jpe
g"` should match. This is fine.\n\n15. **PhotoController `@Patch("reorder")` mis
sing `@HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)`**: Inconsistency with other endpoints.\n\n16. **
BDD setup requiring non-existent matching module**: This is the most critical is
sue causing test failures.\n\nLet me check if there\'s a global validation pipe.
',
    encrypted=None
)
