t the BDD setup, it mocks the guard, implying it should be used somewhere. The d
ocs mention it should be on matching/chat routes. Without the matching module ex
isting, there\'s nowhere to mount it yet.\n\n3. **API Contract mismatch for Crea
te vs Update Profile**: The OpenAPI contract `profile.yaml` uses `UpdateProfileR
equest` for both `POST` and `PATCH`. The backend has `CreateProfileDto` (require
d fields) and `UpdateProfileDto` (all optional). Since the generated mobile code
only has `UpdateProfileRequest`, the mobile sends the same DTO for both create a
nd update. This is a contract-level issue: the contract should define separate s
chemas or make `UpdateProfileRequest` not have required fields if it\'s used for
PATCH.\n\nActually, wait - for POST, having required fields in the contract is c
orrect since creation needs all fields. For PATCH, the contract shouldn\'t mark 
